The solvent is treated as a dielectric medium with a relative dielectric permittivity constant er taken as that of water at 298 K, i.e. 78.5. The long-range repulsive electrostatic potential along the distance rij between a charged monomer i and a charged monomer j is described via a screened Debye‚ÄìHu Ãà ckel potential,
